metadata.name: Mona Lisa
metadata.description: Painted between 1503 and 1517, the Mona Lisa is a masterful portrait of a woman whose identity has long been debated. The work is famous for its enigmatic smile and preternatural calm, set against an idealized landscape that recedes through Leonardo’s use of atmospheric perspective. The painting has inspired centuries of admiration, study, and speculation regarding both the sitter and the artist’s technique.
metadata.creator: Leonardo da Vinci
